    <etym xml:lang="ru"><bibl><author>О. Densusianu</author></bibl> (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                >Irano-Romanica I. Grai şi Suflet I, 1924, стр. 242—245</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">Irano-Romanica I. Grai şi Suflet I, 1924, p.
            242—245</biblScope></bibl>) предполагает скифо-иранское <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>čap-</w></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>čapiš</w><gloss><q>годовалый козленок</q></gloss></mentioned>),
        откуда идут, по его мнению, <mentioned xml:lang="ro"><lang/><w>ţap</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sqj"><lang/><w>tsap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="it-x-dial"><lang/><w>tsappo</w><gloss><q>козел</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако
        переход %ip%i → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>w</w></mentioned> представляет трудности.
        Ср., впрочем, %ixaw-yn%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xawyn"/>] из %ikap%i-.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en"><bibl><author>О. Densusianu</author></bibl> (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                >Irano-Romanica I. Grai şi Suflet I, 1924, стр. 242—245</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">Irano-Romanica I. Grai şi Suflet I, 1924, p.
            242—245</biblScope></bibl>) assumes a <mentioned xml:lang=""
            ><lang/><w>čap-</w></mentioned> (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>čapiš</w><gloss><q>year-old kid</q></gloss></mentioned>), откуда
        идут, по его мнению, <mentioned xml:lang="ro"><lang/><w>ţap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sqj"><lang/><w>tsap</w><gloss><q>heberling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="it-x-dial"><lang/><w>tsappo</w><gloss><q>goat</q></gloss></mentioned>. However
        the transition %ip%i → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>w</w></mentioned> present
        difficulties. Cf., however, %ixaw-yn%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xawyn"/>] from
        %ikap%i-.</etym>
</entry>
